>     I remember reading somewhere that the paralell port on some
>PC's is simply a 74374 style latch and cannot take input.  Most
>newer PC's probably have the parallel port integrated into one
>of the three or four VLSI chips that make up a whole motherboard
>these days, though, and those parallel ports should be 
>bi-directional.

There are atleast 4 input lines on a PC parallel port, 
	ACK, BUSY, Paper out

You only need 1 line connected to a coin tossing machine to get a 
random bit stream. Email me if you need to know how to convert a bit
stream into a sequence of bytes (:->

Pete.
